# Frontend images

All images in `apps/frontend` must use the shared base component. Do not use `<img>` or import from `next/image` directly in app code.

## Required

```tsx
import { Image } from "@/components/ui/image";

<div className="relative aspect-square">
  <Image
    src={src}
    alt="Description"
    sizes="(max-width: 640px) 50vw, 320px"
    fit="contain"
  />
</div>
```

- Parent must be `position: relative` (e.g. `className="relative …"`) because `Image` uses `fill`.
- Always pass meaningful `alt` and a realistic `sizes` string.
- Use `fit="cover"` for photo backgrounds; `fit="contain"` for product shots on neutral/dark backgrounds.
- `src` may be `StaticImageData` (import) or `string` (API/CDN URL or public path).

## Forbidden

```tsx
// ❌ Raw HTML
<img src="…" alt="…" />

// ❌ Direct next/image in components, sections, or pages
import Image from "next/image";
```

The only `<img>` in the project lives inside `components/ui/image.tsx` for remote URLs.
